    <p>On Nov 28, my fam­ily and I were at a mall near my home when my hus­band sud­denly re­alised that he had for­got­ten to turn off the stove.</p>
    <p>When we rushed back, two fire en­gines were al­ready at the scene, and the chil­dren and I were hys­ter­i­cal.</p>
    <p>A young Sin­ga­pore Civil</p>
    <p>De­fence Force (SCDF) of­fi­cer calmed us down while the oth­ers darted up to my flat. For­tu­nately, there was only a very charred pot and smoke.</p>
    <p>We would like to ex­press our grat­i­tude to these brave men, and also thank the civic-minded neigh­bours who called for help. Atika Ab­dul­lah Foo</p>


